      },
      {
        id: 'balat',
        coords: [41.0343, 28.9497],
        location: 'Balat, Fatih',
        title: 'Between Heritage and Instagram',
        text: `Balatâ€™s colorful facades attract visitors, but behind the photos are synagogues, churches, and long-standing Jewish, Greek, and Armenian histories. New cafes run by recent migrants add to the soundscape â€” Arabic pop next to Turkish rock, Hebrew greetings remembered by elders. Locals warn that the areaâ€™s visibility is a double-edged sword: tourism brings income, but raises rents and erodes the fragile social fabric.`,
