      },
      // --- New demo pins ---
      {
        id: 'karakoy_pier',
        coords: [41.0226, 28.9784],
        location: 'KarakÃ¶y Ä°skelesi, BeyoÄŸlu',
        title: 'Crossing Currents: Ferries, Fish, and Faith',
        text: `Between the pier and the fish stalls, KarakÃ¶y mixes office workers, tourists, and long-time residents. Calls to prayer blend with ferry announcements; seagulls circle above simit sellers. The waterfront is a daily ritual â€” a threshold where arrivals and departures make the city feel both stable and in motion.`,
